🔉#SOUNDON: We’re going green for our #digestion 💚😍 Treat your #gut with this Garden Greens Soup! The leafy greens in it are a good source of #fiber, that can help the growth of #healthy gut #bacteria. 
Full Recipe: 
1 bunch kale (8-10 whole leaves)
3 ½ cups chicken or vegetable broth
½ bunch fresh parsley, leaves only, coarsely chopped (about 1 cup, loosely packed)
3 cups fresh spinach leaves (about 3 ounces)
2 cups broccoli florets (about 5 ounces)
1 large carrot, coarsely grated
3 green onions (both white and green parts), roughly chopped
2 large garlic cloves, roughly chopped
2 TBSP white miso paste, or to taste
Juice of half a lemon, or to taste
1/4 TSP red pepper flakes
Salt and pepper to taste
4 scoops Herbalife Nutrition Simply Probiotic

Per serving:
Calories:  160
Protein: 13 g
Carbohydrate: 27 g
Fat: 3 g
Fiber: 6.5 g

#Probiotics are excellent for your gut health, and are often found in fermented foods🧄 🥕 🥒 Try making these spicy pickled veggies as a natural source! Learn about probiotics at link in bio. 

Ingredients: 
1 ½ cups cucumber 
1 ½ cups green beans 
1 ½ cups peppers 
3 cups cauliflower 
1 ½ cups carrots 
1 cup pitted green olives 

Aromatic spices per jar: 
1 bay leaf 
½ teaspoon oregano 
¼ teaspoon celery seeds 
¼ teaspoon fennel seeds 
¼ teaspoon mustard seeds 
¼ tsp red pepper flakes* add more for extra spice 
¼ tsp black pepper 
1 tablespoon olive oil 
1 smashed garlic clove 
Fresh dill sprigs pack around outside of jar 

Directions: Divide the cauliflower, sliced carrots, cucumber red bell pepper, and olives between the four jars. Fill them to the top. Set a medium pot over high heat. Add the water, vinegar, salt, and agave syrup. Bring to a boil. Stir well, then carefully pour the boiling brine into each jar.  Allow the pickled vegetables to cool at room temperature. Then cover with a lid, shake, and refrigerate for 36-48 hours before serving. 

Makes four 16 oz jars
~130 calories per jar

#HerbalifeNutrition
